{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:sirach.32",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 32,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 32 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:1",
      "text": "If thou be made the master of a feast, lift not thyself up, but be among them as one of the rest; take diligent care for them, and so sit down.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:2",
      "text": "And when thou hast done all thy office, take thy place, that thou mayest be merry with them, and receive a crown for thy well ordering of the feast.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:3",
      "text": "Speak, thou that art the elder, for it becometh thee, but with sound judgment; and hinder not musick.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:4",
      "text": "Pour not out words where there is a musician, and shew not forth wisdom out of time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:5",
      "text": "A concert of musick in a banquet of wine is as a signet of carbuncle set in gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:6",
      "text": "As a signet of an emerald set in a work of gold, so is the melody of musick with pleasant wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:7",
      "text": "Speak, young man, if there be need of thee: and yet scarcely when thou art twice asked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:8",
      "text": "Let thy speech be short, comprehending much in few words; be as one that knoweth and yet holdeth his tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:9",
      "text": "If thou be among great men, make not thyself equal with them; and when ancient men are in place, use not many words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:10",
      "text": "Before the thunder goeth lightning; and before a shamefaced man shall go favour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:11",
      "text": "Rise up betimes, and be not the last; but get thee home without delay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:12",
      "text": "There take thy pastime, and do what thou wilt: but sin not by proud speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:13",
      "text": "And for these things bless him that made thee, and hath replenished thee with his good things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:14",
      "text": "Whoso feareth the Lord will receive his discipline; and they that seek him early shall find favour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:15",
      "text": "He that seeketh the law shall be filled therewith: but the hypocrite will be offended thereat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:16",
      "text": "They that fear the Lord shall find judgment, and shall kindle justice as a light.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:17",
      "text": "A sinful man will not be reproved, but findeth an excuse according to his will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:18",
      "text": "A man of counsel will be considerate; but a strange and proud man is not daunted with fear, even when of himself he hath done without counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:19",
      "text": "Do nothing without advice; and when thou hast once done, repent not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:20",
      "text": "Go not in a way wherein thou mayest fall, and stumble not among the stones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:21",
      "text": "Be not confident in a plain way.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:22",
      "text": "And beware of thine own children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:23",
      "text": "In every good work trust thy own soul; for this is the keeping of the commandments.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.32.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 32,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 32:24",
      "text": "He that believeth in the Lord taketh heed to the commandment; and he that trusteth in him shall fare never the worse.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
